reviewText: Ten minutes?  Ten lousy minutes?  This is the best they could do for the customer's money?  Ten.  Minutes.
Great photography, but not enough, and to much surmising by the personnel

I got several videos about Petra. My favorite was "Petra: Prophecy Revealed" because of the enormous amount of information in it.

This video was what it was described to be and is a travel video, more secular in nature than my favorite which I mentioned above. The quality and information is good. It's just very short, which surprised me a little. If I had remembered to check the time before I bought it I wouldn't have been surprised. All-in-all, it's a good product and someone watching it will have a good idea of what Petra is all about, with few, if any, Biblical references.
